This paper deals with the complexity of reasoning with disjunctive logic programs, which is a topic that falls under the scope of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the problem, which is related to databases (cs.DB) and complexity theory (cs.CC). Finally, the paper presents results on the complexity of reasoning, which is a topic that can be studied using techniques from data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
